current-chamber.#text: IN THE SENATE OF THE UNITED STATES

quote.#text: National Historically Black Colleges and Universities Week

official-title.#text: Designating the week beginning September 23, 2013, as

cosponsor.#tail: ) submitted the following resolution; which was considered and agreed to

quote.#text:
National
			 Historically Black Colleges and Universities Week

text.#text:
designates the
			 week beginning September 23, 2013, as

calls on the
			 people of the United States and interested groups to observe the week with
			 appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs to demonstrate support for
			 historically Black colleges and universities in the United States.

Whereas there are 106 historically Black colleges and
			 universities in the United States;

Whereas historically Black colleges and universities allow
			 talented and diverse students, many of whom represent underserved populations,
			 to attain their full potential through higher education; and

Whereas the achievements and goals of historically Black
			 colleges and universities are deserving of national recognition: Now,
			 therefore, be it

{http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/}title.#text: 113 SRES 261 ATS: Designating the week beginning September 23, 2013, as “National Historically Black Colleges and Universities Week”.
